!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>First let’s save it on the local storage&nbsp;… we need to add these lines in <strong>my-login.js</strong> in the function handleResponse like this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>if (data.detail.__data.xhr.response.isuser==’True’){</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>localStorage.setItem(“passNumber”,data.detail.__data.xhr.response.passNumber);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>localStorage.setItem(“isuser”,data.detail.__data.xhr.response.isuser);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>this.set(‘route.path’, ‘view1’);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>}else{</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>localStorage.setItem(“isuser”,data.detail.__data.xhr.response.isuser);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>alert(“Your username and password are wrong..”)}</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>now when you login successfully (passNumber, isuser) will the return values and in our example it is (1234321, True)…</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now we need to edit the function to automatic redirect, inside <strong>ready()</strong> add this&nbsp;:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>if (localStorage.getItem(“isuser”)==’True’){</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>this.set(‘route.path’, ‘view1’);</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>console.log(“enter”);</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>};</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now every time you will enter login page the application will check the value if true it will redirect you to the main page <strong>view1</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And now we want to make sure that’s the <strong>passNumber </strong>is saved too, so inside <strong>my-view1.js</strong> we will add this code:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>ready(){</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>super.ready();</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>console.log(“View1”);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>this.passNumber=localStorage.getItem(“passNumber”);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>console.log(this.passNumber);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>}</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>static get properties () {</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>return {</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>passNumber: {</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>type: String</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>}</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>}</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>}</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And in the html just add</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>&lt;h1&gt;View One PassNumber: {{passNumber}}&lt;/h1&gt;</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And try to login again from scratch to test you should get this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*j3QFi0_RNDxGxh2CSat6uA.png\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And try to enter from the URL like this&nbsp;: <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8081/login\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>http://127.0.0.1:8081/login</strong></a> you will be redirect to <strong>view1 </strong>page.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Okay now we want to implement logout functionality&nbsp;…</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Inside <strong>my-app.js</strong> we will add button like this&nbsp;:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*X5YuCE16QRLDu9az2bYFvA.png\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So after <strong>&lt;/iron-selector&gt;</strong> add this code for the button&nbsp;:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>&lt;paper-button raised on-tap=”logout” class=”indigo” style=”background:red;color:#fff;width:80%”&gt;Logout&lt;/paper-button&gt;</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now we have to add these function inside the component:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>constructor(){super();}</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>ready(){super.ready();}</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>static get properties () {</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>return {</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>logout: {</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>type: Function</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>}}}</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>logout(){</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>alert(“False”);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>localStorage.setItem(“isuser”,”False”);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>this.set(‘route.path’, ‘login’);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>}</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And we need to add this inside the HTML:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>&lt;app-location route=”{{route}}”&gt;&lt;/app-location&gt;</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>&lt;app-route route=”{{route}}” pattern=”/:view” data=”{{routeData}}” tail=”{{subroute}}”&gt; &lt;/app-route&gt;</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And don’t forget to import the dependencies library&nbsp;:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>import ‘@polymer/app-route/app-location.js’;</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>import ‘@polymer/app-route/app-route.js’;</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>import ‘@polymer/paper-button/paper-button.js’;</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And now you ready to test <strong>Logout button</strong>&nbsp;…</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*8btqXxMefxJ8E4jMgtOcDA.png\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It should redirect you to login page like this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*0152M-KNT7m_oUXI-C1Qzg.png\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Great….you did it. However, if you go to <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8081/view1\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>http://127.0.0.1:8081/view1</strong></a> direct you will enter without any login and this is vulnerability in the app&nbsp;…so we have to check if you are logged in so you will add this code to <strong>my-app.js</strong> inside <strong>ready()</strong> function:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>if (localStorage.getItem(“isuser”)==’True’){</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>this.set(‘route.path’, ‘view1’);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>}else{</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>this.set(‘route.path’, ‘login’);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>}</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This code will redirect you to login if you are not logged in&nbsp;….</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>GoodLuck bross</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>FullCode:<a href=\"https://github.com/enghamzasalem/polymer-3-starter-kit-with-login-using-node-js\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/enghamzasalem/polymer-3-starter-kit-with-login-using-node-js</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Polymer 3 starter kit with login using Node JS -Part 3', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-06-14 19:04:43', '2019-06-14 18:04:43', '', 16, 'https://enghamzasalem.com/blog/index.php/2019/06/14/16-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
