(127, 1, '2019-11-28 12:41:20', '2019-11-28 12:41:20', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have create the some component in different web component framework (Stencil.js &amp; Polymer 3 &amp; Lit-element) and publish them as npm packages:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/playlist-embed\">https://www.npmjs.com/package/playlist-embed</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/youtubelistembedstencil\">https://www.npmjs.com/package/youtubelistembedstencil</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/youtube-list-embed-lit-element\">https://www.npmjs.com/package/youtube-list-embed-lit-element</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>lets start with <strong>Stencil</strong> form<strong> Ionic Framework</strong>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Stencil is a tool-chain for building reusable, scalable Design Systems. Generate small, blazing fast, and 100% standards based Web Components that run in every browser.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Web Component-based</li><li>Asynchronous rendering pipeline</li><li>Type Script support</li><li>One-way Data Binding</li><li>Component per-rendering</li><li>Simple component lazy-loading</li><li>JSX support</li><li>Dependency-free components</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://stenciljs.com/\">https://stenciljs.com/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the other hand have <strong>polymer 3 </strong>from <strong>Google</strong>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Polymer is an open-source JavaScript library for building web applications using Web Components. The library is being developed by Google developers and contributors on GitHub. Modern design principles are implemented as a separate project using Google’s Material Design design principles.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.polymer-project.org/\">https://www.polymer-project.org/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Finally, we have the new version of polymer called <strong>Lit element</strong> also from <strong>Google</strong>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lit-element is a simple base class for creating fast, lightweight web components that work in any web page with any framework.Lit Element uses lit-HTML to render into shadow DOM, and adds API to manage properties and attributes. Properties are observed by default, and elements update asynchronously when their properties change.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://lit-element.polymer-project.org/\">https://lit-element.polymer-project.org/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What is did i have created the same components in three different technology, lets see the code together&nbsp;:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Lit Element Component:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>// this the element when you want to add it to the page: \n&lt;youtube-list-embed-lit-element      width=\"100%\"      height=\"500px\"      listid=\"PL32HFpx_LBMvvsDUTEBQxIdrmszkfEM0H\"    >&lt;/youtube-list-embed-lit-element></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>and this is the code for the element:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>import {LitElement, html, property} from “lit-element”;</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>class YoutubeListEmbedLitElement extends LitElement {</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>static get properties() { return {width: String, height: String, listid: String}; }</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>render() { return html`</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>&lt;iframe width=${this.width} height=${this.height} src=${“https://www.youtube.com/embed/videoseries?list=” + this.listid} &gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;`;</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>} }</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>customElements.define(“youtube-list-embed-lit-element”, YoutubeListEmbedLitElement);</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Polymer Component&nbsp;:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>// this the element when you want to add it to the page:\n&lt;playlist-embed width=\"100%\" height=\"700\" listid=\"PL32HFpx_LBMvvsDUTEBQxIdrmszkfEM0H\">&lt;/playlist-embed></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>and this is the code for the element:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>import {PolymerElement, html} from “@polymer/polymer/polymer-element.js”;</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>class PlaylistEmbed extends PolymerElement {</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>static get properties() { return { width: { type: String, value: “” }, height: { type: String, value: “” }, listid: { type: URL } }; }</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>static get template() {</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>return html` &lt;iframe width=”[[width]]” height=”[[height]]” src=”https://w