(129, 1, '2019-11-28 12:41:20', '2019-11-28 12:41:20', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have create the some component in different web component framework (Stencil.js &amp; Polymer 3 &amp; Lit-element) and publish them as npm packages:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/playlist-embed\">https://www.npmjs.com/package/playlist-embed</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/youtubelistembedstencil\">https://www.npmjs.com/package/youtubelistembedstencil</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/youtube-list-embed-lit-element\">https://www.npmjs.com/package/youtube-list-embed-lit-element</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>lets start with <strong>Stencil</strong> form<strong> Ionic Framework</strong>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Stencil is a tool-chain for building reusable, scalable Design Systems. Generate small, blazing fast, and 100% standards based Web Components that run in every browser.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Web Component-based</li><li>Asynchronous rendering pipeline</li><li>Type Script support</li><li>One-way Data Binding</li><li>Component per-rendering</li><li>Simple component lazy-loading</li><li>JSX support</li><li>Dependency-free components</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://stenciljs.com/\">https://stenciljs.com/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the other hand have <strong>polymer 3 </strong>from <strong>Google</strong>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Polymer is an open-source JavaScript library for building web applications using Web Components. The library is being developed by Google developers and contributors on GitHub. Modern design principles are implemented as a separate project using Google